eviations:\n  ```json\n  [\"node_filesystem_usage_rate\", \"pod_cpu_usage\", \"client_error_ratio\", \"error_ratio\", \"rrt_max\"]\n  ```\n\n### Hypotheses Generated\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"node_filesystem_usage_rate\", \"pod_cpu_usage\", \"client_error_ratio\", \"error_ratio\", \"rrt_max\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-08\",\n      \"reason\": \"Excessive filesystem usage (node_filesystem_usage_rate) has caused cascading performance impacts on hosted Pods and Services.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Filesystem usage increased from 53.61% to 77.09% with change ratio of 35.92%.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis-cart-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Decreased pod resource availability (pod_cpu_usage), potentially due to Node resource contention on aiops-k8s-08.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"pod_cpu_usage higher at p99 level with change ratio 72.86%.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"Performance degradation marked by increased client_error_ratio and error_ratio.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"client_error_ratio and error_ratio p99 both increased suddenly with a change ratio of 200%. Latency (rrt_max) also significant.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"}
